{
  "message": "feat: add Frankenstein-themed CTA for Spec Evolution Lab on landing page\n\nThe Spec Evolution Lab (/how-it-was-built/spec-evolution-lab) had very low\ndiscoverability \u2014 it was buried in a sub-menu with no visual presence on\nthe main landing page. This adds a prominent, visually striking CTA section\nbetween the terminal demo and the \"Why FrankenTUI\" feature cards.\n\nDesign:\n- Full-width interstitial section with red monster-themed accents (distinct\n  from the green used elsewhere) to signal \"experimental/laboratory\" tone\n- The Frankenstein head (franken-favicon.webp) at h-32/md:h-44 with:\n  - Corner bracket decorations and a pulsing red glow halo\n  - Scanline overlay and flickering red tint for CRT effect\n  - SVG lightning arc animations on hover (two paths with staggered timing)\n  - Hover wiggle/scale via framer-motion whileHover\n- \"Forensic_Node_Live\" pinging status badge\n- FrankenGlitch text effect on the \"SPEC EVOLUTION LAB.\" heading\n- Red neural pulse border animation on the FrankenContainer\n- Electrical grid background pattern with radial mask\n- \"Enter Laboratory\" text with a circular arrow button that fills red\n  on hover\n- The entire section is a single clickable <Link> for maximum hit area\n\nThe section was initially implemented by Claude, then visually enhanced by\na Gemini agent (via linter hook) which added the lightning SVGs, corner\nbrackets, scanline overlays, enlarged dimensions, and refined typography.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
